      "url": "https://csa-content-standards.netlify.app/docs/master-reference#9-claims-validation",
      "standalone_url": "https://csa-content-standards.netlify.app/docs/claims-validation",
      "notes": "Editorial procedures for the CSA built-in fact-checking module. Applicability determined by content pipeline tier: High Touch (HITL) = full application; Semi-Automated = selective; Fully Automated (game scores, weather, United Robots) = not required. Five verdicts: TRUE, FALSE, MISLEADING, INSUFFICIENT_EVIDENCE, OVERGENERALIZED. Two editorial actions: Needs Correction (FALSE, MISLEADING) and Needs Clarification (OVERGENERALIZED, INSUFFICIENT_EVIDENCE). Includes source authority tiers, content-type elevated risk rules, and escalation logic."
